The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 22: The government may reduce its stake in the State Bank of India by 4.4 per cent to 55 per cent from 59.4 per cent with the approval of Parliament, a senior official said. The stake reduction plan would be put before the cabinet soon and the bill seeking to amend the State Bank of India Act, 1955 could be introduced in the current session of Parliament.                            
	 New Delhi, July 22: The government collected Rs 59,465 crore as direct taxes in the first quarter of the current fiscal, an increase of 3.65 per cent over the year-ago period. Direct tax collection, comprising corporate and personal income tax, stood at Rs 57,373 crore during the same period last year.                             
	 Mumbai, July 22: The Reserve Bank today allowed foreign companies to raise money from the Indian stock markets through Indian depository receipts. The RBI has also extended till September 30 the facility to provide liquidity support of Rs 20,000 crore to non-deposit taking NBFCs.                            
	 Mumbai, July 22: Sebi has asked the stock exchanges to immediately bar listed companies from issuing shares with superior rights in terms of voting or dividend compared with the rights on shares that are already listed. Sebi has decided to amend the equity listing agreement with immediate effect.                             
	 New Delhi, July 22: The Prime Ministers office is believed to have asked for urgent comments from the petroleum ministry, which has been accused by industrialist Anil Ambani of siding with RIL in the ongoing gas dispute.                                                                                                                           
